 Appearances (Goals). Karlen Abramov (Armenian:  , born on 9 May 1987 in Tashkent, Uzbek SSR) was a Jewish[1]-Armenian professional football striker. His first trainer was Viktor Chuchvarin and his father Vadim Abramov ex-coach of Uzbekistani Olympic Team, the current manager of Uzbekistan national football teams. He died in a car accident in Tashkent [1]. The 21-year old player was transferred to the hospital in critical condition and doctors werent able to save his life. In July 2008, Abramov was set to trial with Maccabi Tel Aviv in Israel.[2] 
